WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Undercover:  Is this a warehouse that you use alone?
Health Food Center owner:  We only do the butchering here.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Owner lifts up a tent.  There is a big cage hidden underneath it.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:23.000
The cage is full of cats.  But why are these cats hidden?

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:31.000
Owner:  The reason why we hide them is because people who likes animal gets upset.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Cats are crowded into one corner.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:42.000
The owner selects a few of them and orders her butcher to “work” on them.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
The butcher starts to take cats out of the cage using snare.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:58.000
Cat strangled with rope around her neck is trying to get away but she can’t.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:04.000
And then the “work” begins inside.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:10.000
The “work” means killing and getting cats ready to make into soup.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Butchered cats are put into a big plastic basin.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Butcher delivers the cats to the Health Food Center.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:30.000
At the Health Food Center, cats are washed and put into the pressure cooker in one piece.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:38.000
And then arthritis Chinese herbal medicine and water is poured into the cooker and boiled together.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:45.000
After boiling for almost 24 hours, the cat soup -  known to be the miracle cure for arthritis – becomes  completed.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:51.000
The owner boasts about the effectiveness of the cat soup.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Owner:  We will make it for you with care.  We have a separate list of customers who order nothing but  cats.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:05.000
The owner is showing us a notebook with the list of name of regular customers who only orders cat soup.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:11.000
We have customer who comes all the way from Busan through hearing our reputation.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
We have customers coming all the way from Seoul, Busan and even from Changryeong.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:23.000
The notebook has a list of customers, contact info and their order details.
“Cat-3, dog legs-2, 160,000 Korean won ($150 USD) ”
“Only cats-2”

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:29.000
The owner boasts that their customer list is a proof that the cat soup is effective.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Boiled for 24 hours, after squeezing everything including the bones, it becomes cat soup.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:41.000
They tell us the cats used for these soup are different.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:46.000
Owner:  These are not pet cats.  They are stray cats.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:59.000
Undercover: Are they ok to eat?
Owner:  Dog farmers bring cats to us when they bring dogs.

